	        Send us your pictures   ·  Send us your stories Lagos - Officials say rescue efforts have ended at the scene where a four-story residential building collapsed and killed at least eight people in Nigeria's largest city. Kehinde Adebayo with the Lagos State Emergency Management Agency said on Wednesday afternoon that rescuers are giving way to investigators who will seek the cause of the collapse.   24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  